('19950300117', '199503001', 17, '(a)Functions f and g are defined by;\\[f:x \\mapsto \\frac{6}{(x-2)},x\\neq 2\\] \\[g:x \\mapsto kx^2-1\\] where k is a constant.;(i)Given that gf(5) = 7, evaluate k.;(ii)Express \\[f^2(x) \\]  in the form \\[\\frac{(ax+b)}{(c-x)}\\] stating the values of a, b and c.;(b)On graph paper, using the same scale on each axis, draw the graph of \\[h:x \\mapsto \\frac{(2x+2)}{(x+2)}\\] for the domain \\[-1<=x<=3\\];(i) By drawing the appropriate straight line on the graph obtain a solution of the equation \\[h(x)=h^{-1}(x)\\];(ii) State the domain of\\[h^{-1}(x)\\];iii)Using the same axes as for h(x), draw, on the same diagram, the graph of \\[h^{-1}(x)\\]', 'Exam', 52, 5201, 6, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
