('19950400103', '199504001', 3, 'a) Express \\[63\\sin x+16\\cos x\\]in the form \\[R\\sin \\left ( x+\\alpha  \\right )\\] where R is positive and \\[\\alpha\\] is acute.;Find ;i)	the acute angle x for which $$63\\sin x+16\\cos x =50$$;ii)	the obtuse angle x for which \\[63\\sin x+16\\cos x=0\\];b) By first expressing \\[\\cos 3x\\]as \\[\\cos \\left ( 2x+x \\right )\\]show that \\[\\cos 3x -=4\\cos ^{3}x-3\\cos x\\]Hence find all the angles between \\[0^{\\circ}\\]and \\[360^{\\circ}\\]which satisfy the equation \\[\\cos 3x +\\cos ^{2}x=0\\];(Note: Please enter the answers in ascending order)', 'Exam', 45, 4501, 1, NULL, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
